            "id": "4561253",
            "title": "Canadian Pacific Kansas City subsidiary raises $1.2B via debt offering",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><span>Canadian Pacific Kansas City (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CP\" title=\"Canadian Pacific Kansas City Limited\">CP</a></span></span></span></span>) said that its wholly-owned subsidiary, <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20424878-cpkc-announces-us-1_2-billion-debt-offering\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Canadian Pacific Railway Company\">Canadian Pacific Railway Company</a>, is issuing $600M of 4.000% notes due 2029 and $600M of 5.500% notes due 2056.</span></li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">\n<span>The offering is expected to close on March 6, 2026.</span><span></span>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">\n<span>Proceeds from the offering will be used primarily to refinance debt and for general corporate purposes.</span><span></span>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><span>The stock closed lower at $118.41 CAD during the trading session.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
