            "id": "4561273",
            "title": "BitFuFu says February bitcoin production slips slightly; holds 1,830 BTC",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.globenewswire.com/Tracker?data=8U4ZOrGsZHhN6GC02JarJezccq8LQCeR4zeBIyglOdwZfACnkACHkn8HMWLTCbKOZuGZMpLGO4oZfaeD4n8aeA==\" rel=\"nofollow\">BitFuFu</a> (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ: <span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FUFU\" title=\"BitFuFu Inc.\">FUFU</a></span></span>) on Thursday said its unaudited bitcoin production for February 2026 totaled 227 BTC, slightly down from 229 BTC in January.</li>\n<li>The company said daily bitcoin production rose to 8.1 BTC from 7.4 BTC in the prior month.</li>\n<li>BitFuFu held 1,830 BTC as of Feb. 28, up from 1,796 BTC at the end of January.</li>\n<li>Self-mining production fell to 37 BTC from 46 BTC, while cloud-mining production increased to 190 BTC from 183 BTC.</li>\n<li>Total hashrate under management declined to 26.4 EH/s from 29.6 EH/s in January, including 3.6 EH/s of self-owned hashrate and 22.8 EH/s from third-party suppliers and hosting customers.</li>\n<li>Power capacity under management decreased to 463 MW from 520 MW a month earlier.</li>\n<li>FUFU closed <span>+6.25%</span> at $2.72.</li>\n<li>Source: <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20425571-bitfufu-announces-february-2026-bitcoin-production-and-operational-updates\">Press Release</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
